5000 is risky on our slow jenkins machines (or a community user compiling while something else is running on his/her machine).
I recommend just adding a @Timeout(600_000) on the test itself and do
while (solverManager.getSolverStatus(problemId) != expectedStatusChange) {
   Thread.sleep(100L);
}
return;

Calling currentTimeMillis() every 5 milliseconds might not be as cheap as one would expect. And questionable on Windows that has a 17 millisecond clock granularity :)

